<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1436,1690,1861]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1690,1716]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Comments</emphasis>
. This name was considered an unassigned position within 
<emphasis box="[931,1101,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[931,1063,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Augochlora</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1101,1690,1716]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Hurd, P. D." box="[1142,1389,1690,1717]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" refId="ref76175" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Hurd, P. D. (1987) An Annotated Catalog of the Halictid Bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., 405 pp." type="book" year="1987">Moure &amp; Hurd (1987)</bibRefCitation>
and unplaced by Moure (2007). The 
<typeStatus box="[520,568,1727,1753]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">type</typeStatus>
is also probably lost and the identity of this species is uncertain considering only the male original description. As for the previous name, we did not find any clues about the identity of this species and its generic placement among augochlorines. For minimizing changes we keep this species as unplaced within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[230,362,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
